Link to wireframe image: https://imgur.com/a/simple-web-stack-lin00Kv
You must be able to explain some specifics about this infrastructure:
    What is a server -> This is the main computer that hosts all the components of the stack.

    What is the role of the domain name -> It provides a human readable address to access the website. It points to the server Ip address `8.8.8.8` in this simple web stack.

    What type of DNS record www is in www.foobar.com -> Cname records.

    What is the role of the web server -> The web server handles incoming http requests and returns static content, or passes it  to the application server to handle dynamic requests.

    What is the role of the application server -> It hosts the application files and processes dynamic contents, it executes the logic, interacts with the db, and generate responses to be sent back to the web server.

    What is the role of the database -> The db(MySql) stores the app data, like User information and other relevant data.

    What is the server using to communicate with the computer of the user requesting the website -> Http

